de.rojer.editablefiles

Class EditableFile

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.rojer.editablefiles.EditableFile

  • public class EditableFile
extends java.lang.Object
    This class can be used to read from and write to text files. It uses standard ASCII encoding (total of 127 characters). You can write/read: Integers, Booleans, Floats, Doubles and normal Strings. You can change the encoding of every file to prevent "normal" people from reading your files.
    Version:
    17.3.2019
    Author:
    Rojer
